SQL Server Agent Jobs: An automated execution engine that runs scheduled tasks, scripts, and administrative workflows in the background based on predefined triggers or times.

PowerShell Scripts: Command-line automation scripts used to programmatically manage, configure, and monitor multiple SQL Server instances and operating system resources simultaneously.

Maintenance Plans: A built-in, visual workflow wizard in SQL Server used to easily schedule routine database health tasks like backups, index rebuilds, and integrity checks without writing code.
